## <a id='major-features'></a> New Features in <%= vars.ops_manager %> <%= vars.v_major_version %>

<%= vars.ops_manager %> <%= vars.v_major_version %> includes the following major features:

### <a id='resource-config'></a> Resource Config Redesign

<%= vars.ops_manager %> <%= vars.v_major_version %> introduces a redesigned **Resource Config** pane. The new **Resource Config** pane appears in every <%= vars.ops_manager %> product tile, including BOSH Director.

In the redesigned **Resource Config** pane, you can expand the row that contains each job to reveal additional configuration options. The additional options that you can configure depend on your IaaS. For example, if you use vSphere, you can configure NSX-T or NSX-V settings within each job row.

The new <%= vars.ops_manager %> **Resource Config** pane also has improved error handling. When there is an error, <%= vars.ops_manager %> displays both a banner and an error message next to the field that contains the error. When a value you enter violates the constraints of a job, <%= vars.ops_manager %> highlights the corresponding **Instances**, **VM Type**, and **Persistent Disk Type** fields and displays an error message about the violation.

For more information, see the _Resource Config_ section of the BOSH Director configuration topic for your IaaS:

- [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/om/aws/config-manual.html#pcfaws-om-rscestem)
- [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/om/aws/config-terraform.html#pcfaws-om-rscestem)
