### <a id="cron"></a> Valid cron Input Verification

For `string` type form fields in tiles, <%= vars.ops_manager %> supports a `constraints.must_be_cron_schedule` attribute that verifies whether the input is a valid `cron` expression. Tiles can use this attribute for fields that schedule backups, for example. For information about the `string` blueprint type, see [string](http://docs.pivotal.io/tiledev/property-template-references.html#string) in _Property and Template References_ in the <%= vars.platform_name %> Tile Developer Guide.

### <a id='sanitize-certs'></a> <%= vars.ops_manager %> Sanitizes Certificate Input for Carriage Returns and Line Feeds

When you reset the value of a certificate in an <%= vars.ops_manager %> tile, <%= vars.ops_manager %> sanitizes the certificate for carriage returns and line feeds. This prevents BOSH from interpreting the certificate you reset as a new certificate and recreating VMs. You do not need to manually remove newline characters such as `\n`.

### <a id='all-certs'></a> API Call Returns All Certs

Calling the <%= vars.ops_manager %> API `deployed/certificates` endpoint returns listings for the root certificate authority (CA), NATS CA, and certificates that <%= vars.ops_manager %> stores in CredHub, in addition to leaf-level certificates that <%= vars.ops_manager %> stores directly.

For more information, see [List All RSA Certificates](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/security/pcf-infrastructure/managing-certificates.html#list-rsa-certs) in _Managing Certificates with the <%= vars.ops_manager %> API_.

### <a id='download-support-zip'></a> Download a Platform Information Bundle from the <%= vars.ops_manager %> UI or API

You can download a Platform Information Bundle as a ZIP file from the <%= vars.ops_manager %> UI or API. The bundle includes <%= vars.ops_manager %> logs, deployed manifests and configurations, and BOSH deployment diagnostics.

The contents of the bundle help Pivotal Support more quickly address any issues in your deployment.

To download the ZIP file from the UI, click **Support** in the footer of any page in the <%= vars.ops_manager %> UI.

To download the ZIP file from the <%= vars.ops_manager %> API, use the `/api/v0/support_bundle` endpoint. For more information, see [Support Bundle](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/opsman-api/#support-bundle) in the <%= vars.ops_manager %> API documentation.

### <a id='audit-logs'></a> BOSH Director Access Events Appear in Syslog Output

Syslog output includes BOSH Director access events when syslog is enabled in <%= vars.ops_manager %>.

BOSH Director access events correspond to the execution of BOSH CLI commands. The addition of these events allows you to audit BOSH Director access and activity for security monitoring purposes.

For more information, see [Syslog](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/customizing/pcf-interface.html#syslog) in _Using the <%= vars.ops_manager %> Interface_ and [Logging API Access](https://bosh.io/docs/director-access-events/) in the BOSH documentation.

### <a id='audit-user-activity'></a> Request Parameters in <%= vars.ops_manager %> User Activity Logs

The <%= vars.ops_manager %> `audit_log.txt` file includes request parameters. This provides additional information about requests made in the <%= vars.ops_manager %> UI, such as the timestamp of the request and the username that made the request.

These request parameters improve <%= vars.ops_manager %> logs for auditing user activity.

To access the `audit_log.txt` file, SSH into the <%= vars.ops_manager %> VM and navigate to `/var/log/opsmanager/audit_log.txt`.

For more information about the types of user activity that you can audit in the <%= vars.ops_manager %> logs, see [Auditing User Activity in <%= vars.ops_manager %>](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/opsguide/auditing-ops-man.html).

